{
  "id": "sys-10-client-health-monitoring",
  "name": "SYS 05 — Client Health Monitoring",
  "description": "Runs every Monday 8AM EST. Fetches active clients (closed_won, invoice_sent, paid), computes health score from contact recency and invoice status, writes score to HubSpot deal property client_health_score. If below CONFIG threshold, sends Google Chat alert so the team can follow up.",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## SYS 05 — Client Health Monitoring\n\n**Trigger:** Every Monday 8AM EST (cron).\n\n**What it does:** Fetches active clients (closed_won, invoice_sent, paid), computes a health score from recency of contact and invoice status, writes the score to the HubSpot deal property `client_health_score`. If score is below CONFIG's health warning threshold, sends a Google Chat alert so the team can follow up. Keeps at-risk clients visible.\n\n**Dependencies:** CONFIG, HubSpot, Send Google Chat Alert, Log.",
        "height": 300,
        "width": 460,
        "color": 5
      },
      "id": "note-sys10",
      "name": "Note — About this workflow",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1.3,
      "position": [
        80,
        80
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "rule": {
          "interval": [
            {
              "field": "cronExpression",
              "expression": "0 8 * * 1"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "id": "sys10-trigger",
      "name": "Every Monday 8AM EST",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.scheduleTrigger",
      "typeVersion": 1.3,
      "position": [
        250,
        300
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "source": "database",
        "workflowId": {
          "__rl": true,
          "value": "1eTTVoSFSlSPvZV4",
          "mode": "id"
        }
      },
      "id": "sys10-config",
      "name": "Get Config",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.executeWorkflow",
      "typeVersion": 1.3,
      "position": [
        470,
        300
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "resource": "deal",
        "operation": "getAll",
        "filters": {
          "values": [
            {
              "propertyName": "dealstage",
              "operator": "IN",
              "value": "closed_won,invoice_sent,paid"
            }
          ]
        },
        "limit": 100,
        "options": {
          "properties": [
            "dealname",
            "dealstage",
            "tier",
            "contact_email",
            "contact_firstname",
            "last_activity_date",
            "client_health_score",
            "monthly_retainer"
          ]
        }
      },
      "id": "sys10-get-clients",
      "name": "Get Active Clients",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.hubspot",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        690,
        300
      ],
      "credentials": {
        "hubspotApi": {
          "id": "volH6pGD5psvPC7a",
          "name": "HubSpot App Token"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "mode": "combine",
        "combineBy": "combineAll",
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "sys10-merge-config-deals",
      "name": "Merge Deals + Config",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.merge",
      "typeVersion": 3,
      "position": [
        800,
        300
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "// Each item = HubSpot deal merged with CONFIG (n8n 2.x / task runner only resolves $('...') from nodes that connect to this Code node)\nconst CONFIG_KEYS = ['owner', 'pipeline', 'hunter', 'google', 'branding', 'timing', 'scoring', 'leadSourcing', 'tiers', 'industries', 'leadSourcingQueries'];\nfunction pickConfig(j) {\n  const o = {};\n  for (const k of CONFIG_KEYS) {\n    if (j[k] !== undefined) o[k] = j[k];\n  }\n  return o;\n}\nconst now = new Date();\nreturn $input.all().map(({ json: j }) => {\n  const config = pickConfig(j);\n  if (!config.scoring) throw new Error('Missing CONFIG on merged items — check Merge Deals + Config (inputs 0=deals, 1=Get Config)');\n  const p = j.properties || j;\n  let score = 0;\n  const lastContact = p.last_activity_date ? new Date(p.last_activity_date) : null;\n  const daysSinceContact = lastContact ? (now - lastContact) / (24 * 60 * 60 * 1000) : 999;\n  if (daysSinceContact < 7) score += 3;\n  else if (daysSinceContact <= 14) score += 1;\n  else score -= 2;\n  const invoiceOverdue = p.dealstage === 'invoice_sent';\n  if (invoiceOverdue) score -= 3;\n  return {\n    json: {\n      dealId: j.id,\n      clientName: p.dealname || '',\n      tier: p.tier || '',\n      contactEmail: p.contact_email || '',\n      contactFirstName: p.contact_firstname || '',\n      healthScore: score,\n      daysSinceContact: Math.round(daysSinceContact),\n      lastContactDate: lastContact ? lastContact.toISOString().split('T')[0] : 'Never',\n      isWarning: score < config.scoring.healthScoreWarningThreshold,\n      config\n    }\n  };\n});"
      },
      "id": "sys10-calc",
      "name": "Calculate Health Scores",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        910,
        300
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "resource": "deal",
        "operation": "update",
        "dealId": "={{ $json.dealId }}",
        "updateFields": {
          "customPropertiesUi": {
            "customPropertiesValues": [
              {
                "property": "client_health_score",
                "value": "={{ $json.healthScore }}"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "sys10-update-hs",
      "name": "Update HubSpot Score",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.hubspot",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        1130,
        300
      ],
      "credentials": {
        "hubspotApi": {
          "id": "volH6pGD5psvPC7a",
          "name": "HubSpot App Token"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "conditions": {
          "options": {
            "caseSensitive": true,
            "leftValue": "",
            "typeValidation": "strict"
          },
          "conditions": [
            {
              "id": "is-warning",
              "leftValue": "={{ $json.isWarning }}",
              "rightValue": true,
              "operator": {
                "type": "boolean",
                "operation": "equals"
              }
            }
          ],
          "combinator": "and"
        },
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "sys10-check-warning",
      "name": "Below Threshold?",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.if",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        1350,
        300
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const d = $input.first().json;\n\nreturn [{\n  json: {\n    message: `Client health warning: ${d.clientName} — Score ${d.healthScore}. Last contact: ${d.lastContactDate}`,\n    priority: 'warning'\n  }\n}];"
      },
      "id": "sys10-warn-prep",
      "name": "Prep Warning Alert",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        1570,
        200
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "source": "parameter",
        "workflowId": "REPLACE_WITH_SEND_GOOGLE_CHAT_ALERT_WORKFLOW_ID"
      },
      "id": "sys10-warn",
      "name": "Send Warning",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.executeWorkflow",
      "typeVersion": 1.3,
      "position": [
        1790,
        200
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const d = $input.first().json;\n\nreturn [{\n  json: {\n    to: d.contactEmail,\n    subject: `Quick check-in — ${d.clientName}`,\n    html: `<p>Hi ${d.contactFirstName || 'there'},</p><p>Just wanted to check in and make sure everything is running smoothly on your end. It's been a bit since we last connected.</p><p>Is there anything you need from us? Any questions about the systems we've built? Any new processes you'd like to automate?</p><p>Happy to jump on a quick call anytime: ${d.config.owner.calendarLink}</p><p>— John<br/>${d.config.owner.companyName}</p>`,\n    workflowName: 'SYS 05 — Client Health Monitoring'\n  }\n}];"
      },
      "id": "sys10-checkin-prep",
      "name": "Prep Check-in Email",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        2010,
        200
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "source": "parameter",
        "workflowId": "REPLACE_WITH_SEND_EMAIL_WORKFLOW_ID"
      },
      "id": "sys10-checkin",
      "name": "Send Check-in",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.executeWorkflow",
      "typeVersion": 1.3,
      "position": [
        2230,
        200
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "operation": "append",
        "documentId": {
          "mode": "id",
          "value": "={{ $json.config.google.masterSheetId }}"
        },
        "sheetName": {
          "mode": "name",
          "value": "Clients"
        },
        "columns": {
          "mappingMode": "defineBelow",
          "value": {
            "Client Name": "={{ $json.clientName }}",
            "Tier": "={{ $json.tier }}",
            "MRR": "=0",
            "Start Date": "",
            "Last Activity": "={{ $json.lastContactDate }}",
            "Health Score": "={{ $json.healthScore }}"
          }
        },
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "sys10-sheets",
      "name": "Update Clients Tab",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets",
      "typeVersion": 4,
      "position": [
        1570,
        450
      ],
      "credentials": {
        "googleSheetsOAuth2Api": {
          "id": "IJzDJS1jpbItegZD",
          "name": "Google Sheets account 2"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "return [{\n  json: {\n    workflowName: 'SYS 05 — Client Health Monitoring',\n    contactName: $input.first().json.clientName,\n    phone: '',\n    eventType: 'health_check',\n    status: 'success',\n    notes: `Score: ${$input.first().json.healthScore}`\n  }\n}];"
      },
      "id": "sys10-log-prep",
      "name": "Prep Log",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        1790,
        450
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "source": "parameter",
        "workflowId": "REPLACE_WITH_LOG_WORKFLOW_ID"
      },
      "id": "sys10-log",
      "name": "Log to Sheet",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.executeWorkflow",
      "typeVersion": 1.3,
      "position": [
        2010,
        450
      ]
    }
  ],
